title: MQM’s Muhammad Muaz Mehboob wins PS-127 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Muttahidda Qaumi Movement’s (MQM) Muhammad Muaz Mehboob has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-127 Karachi Central-VI by securing 23,389 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Jamat-e-Islami candidate Muhammad Masood Ali, who bagged 12,642 votes.
Voters’ turn-out remained 25.81 %.
